ZH: 他每天早上都会剃须。
EN: He shaves every morning.

ZH: 妈妈建议我剃掉胡子。
EN: My mom suggested I shave off my beard.

ZH: 他剃得很干净。
EN: He shaves very cleanly.

ZH: 他一边喝咖啡一边剃胡子。
EN: He shaves while drinking coffee.

ZH: 我忘记剃胡子了。
EN: I forgot to shave.

ZH: 剃须刀需要更换刀头。
EN: The razor needs a new blade.

ZH: 他喜欢用电动剃须刀。
EN: He likes to use an electric shaver.

ZH: 你会帮我找一把剃刀吗？
EN: Can you help me find a razor?

ZH: 剃掉头发后，他看起来更年轻了。
EN: He looks younger after shaving his hair.

ZH: 我还没有时间去剃毛。
EN: I haven't had time to shave my legs.

ZH: 剃毛可以让皮肤感觉更光滑。
EN: Shaving can make your skin feel smoother.

ZH: 总是要小心不要剃伤皮肤。
EN: Always be careful not to cut the skin when shaving.

ZH: 我不喜欢剃大胡子，觉得会很不舒服。
EN: I don't like shaving big beards, I think it's uncomfortable.

ZH: 我用了新的剃毛霜，皮肤感觉很柔软。
EN: I used a new shaving cream, and my skin feels very soft.

ZH: 我每周都会剃一次胡子。
EN: I shave my beard once a week.

ZH: 剃毛刀对皮肤的刺激较小。
EN: Shaving razors cause less irritation to the skin.

ZH: 那个剃毛刀非常锋利。
EN: That razor is very sharp.

ZH: 剃胡子太痛了！
EN: Shaving the beard hurts too much!

ZH: 他的梳子旁边有一把剃刀。
EN: There is a razor next to his comb.

ZH: 我真的需要一把新的剃须刀。
EN: I really need a new razor.
